<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbbd73f92-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s2015a"><num value="2015a">§ 2015a.</num><heading> Cold standby</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary is authorized to expend such funds as may be necessary for the purposes of maintaining enrichment capability at the Portsmouth, Ohio, facility.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbbd73f93-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/act/1946-08-01/ch724">Aug. 1, 1946, ch. 724</ref>, title I, § 242, as added <ref href="/us/pl/107/222/s1/d/1">Pub. L. 107–222, § 1(d)(1)</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1336">116 Stat. 1336</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
